 .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Fettiplace was born in 1295, in Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Sir John de Brocas about 1309, in Berkshire, England. They were the parents of at least 4 sons and 2 daughters. She died in 1356, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1295–1356":"1295–1356","1290–1365":"1290–1365","1319–1365":"1319–1365","1320–1383":"1320–1383","1321–1352":"1321–1352","1323–1361":"1323–1361","1330–1395":"1330–1395","1352":"1352","1330":"1330","1395":"1395","1295":"1295","1361":"1361","1383":"1383","1290":"1290","about 1309":"umbes 1309","about 1319":"umbes 1319","1356":"1356","1323":"1323","ABT 1321":"umbes 1321","1321":"1321","1365":"1365","1320":"1320","Abt 1330":"umbes 1330","about 1323":"umbes 1323","about 1321":"umbes 1321","1319":"1319","Sherborne St John, Hampshire, England":"Sherborne St John, Hampshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Southampton, , Hampshire, England":"Southampton, Hampshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, England","Beaurepaire, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom":"Beaurepaire, Hampshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Beauparie, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1295–1356":"1295–1356","1290–1365":"1290–1365","1319–1365":"1319–1365","1320–1383":"1320–1383","1321–1352":"1321–1352","1323–1361":"1323–1361","1330–1395